HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 542
By Atchley
A RESOLUTION to recognize Pigeon Forge City Manager Earlene
Teaster on the occasion of her retirement.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those citizens who have performed with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm
throughout their years of public service; and
WHEREAS, Earlene Teaster is one such estimable individual, who has served for forty-
four years as city manager of Pigeon Forge, from which position she is taking her much-
deserved retirement on June 30, 2025; and
WHEREAS, a native of Sevier County, Ms. Teaster is distinguished by being the first
woman to serve as a city manager in the State of Tennessee; having taken up the post of
Pigeon Forge city manager in 1980, she is also the longest-serving city manager in the State's
history; and
WHEREAS, her service to her hometown of Pigeon Forge spans sixty-three years in
total, as she was first hired as city clerk in 1961, before advancing to serve as city recorder; and
WHEREAS, Earlene Teaster's impact on the City of Pigeon Forge is immeasurable; she
recognized the gateway city's potential and has been a strong advocate for supporting tourism,
the city's only industry, through partnership with local businesses and improved infrastructure;
and
WHEREAS, Ms. Teaster guided efforts to establish new businesses, including
Dollywood theme park, Tennessee's most visited ticketed attraction, in 1986, as well as the
LeConte Center at Pigeon Forge in 2013 and the Ripken Experience Pigeon Forge in 2016; and
